Hi Parent_D—happy to clarify in a bit more detail.

Core daily schedule (typical weekday)
- Drop-off window: morning staggered drop-off (we can accommodate a short window; tell me your needed times and I’ll confirm fit).
- Morning: free play + welcome routine, then circle time (songs/story) and small-group activities.
- Outdoor time: daily (weather permitting), typically late morning and/or mid-afternoon.
- Lunch: midday.
- Nap/quiet time: after lunch (quiet rest for all; children who don’t sleep can do calm activities).
- Pick-up window: afternoon staggered pick-up (again, share your needed times and I’ll confirm what we can support; extended-care options depend on demand).

Teacher-to-child ratio
- We staff to maintain close supervision and small-group work; ratios vary slightly by age group. If you share your child’s age, I can give you the exact classroom ratio and typical group size.

Settling-in approach (new children)
- Gradual transition when possible: short initial days, then building up to full days.
- Consistent key-person/primary educator to anchor the child.
- Predictable routines + comfort items allowed.
- Frequent check-ins with families during the first 2–3 weeks (what’s working, drop-off strategies, sleep/eating patterns).

Family commitments we value most
- Reliable communication (sharing changes at home, health/allergy info, and quick responsiveness to messages).
- Consistent routines (on-time drop-off/pick-up, supporting sleep/toileting plans where relevant).
- Partnership mindset: we don’t require volunteering, but we welcome it; the biggest “commitment” is collaborative communication and consistency.

If you’re comfortable sharing: your child’s age, any nap needs, and your required drop-off/pick-up times. Also, where does Nursery_E sit for you right now (backup vs. realistic option this round)?
